-- Given Imaging Slumps Most in 7 Months as Sales Trail Estimates
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-09T21:31:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/given-imaging-slumps-most-in-7-months-as-sales-trail-estimates.html
Given Imaging Ltd. (GIVN)  slid the most in
seven months in New York after the maker of swallowable pill-
sized cameras reported first-quarter sales that trailed
analysts’ predictions.  Given retreated 5.6 percent to $17.69 by 4 p.m. in New
York, the sharpest drop since Sept. 30 and the lowest level in
three months. The stock trades at a discount of 37 cents below
its  Tel Aviv shares , which slipped 2.9 percent to 69.02 shekels
today, or the equivalent of $18.06.  The Yoqneam, Israel-based company said revenue grew 4.7
percent to $42 million in the first three months of the year,
falling short of a median  estimate  of $43.5 million from three
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg. Net income retreated to $201,000
from $677,000 a year earlier, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
